Reasoning: The paper presents a new family of Ising models and proposes a polynomial time algorithm for solving exact inference and sampling. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) for the study of combinatorial structures, Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) for the development of efficient algorithms, Information Theory (cs.IT) for the analysis of information processing systems, Computational Complexity (cs.CC) for the investigation of the computational complexity of problems, and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) for the study of network structures.
